<TEXT>
   Sir Yehudi Menuhin, the violin virtuoso and
conductor, will receive a medal in West Germany for his efforts to
foster Jewish-Christian dialogue and reconciliation after World War
II.
   Menuhin will receive the Buber-Rosenzweig medal in Bonn on March
