<FIRST>r i PM-Japan-FuneralGlance     02-23 0363</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Japan-Funeral Glance,0376</SECOND>
<HEAD>Hirohito Funeral Schedule At-A-Glance</HEAD>
<HEAD>PM-Hirohito Funeral, Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here are the main events for the funeral of Emperor
Hirohito Friday (Thursday and Friday EST):
   _7:30 a.m. (5:30 p.m. EST Thursday) _ Ceremony of farewell at
Imperial Palace with imperial family relatives.
   _9:00 a.m. (7 p.m. EST) _ Coffin is placed in the hearse.
   _9:30 a.m. (7:30 p.m. EST) _ Procession by motorcade from palace
to funeral site at Shinjuku Imperial Gardens, passing through front
gates of Parliament building along the way.
   _10:15 a.m. (8:15 p.m. EST) _ Motorcade arrives at funeral site.
   _10:31 a.m. (8:31 p.m. EST) _ Coffin moved from hearse to bier,
procession on foot to funeral hall.
   _10:40 a.m. (8:40 p.m. EST) _ Procession arrives at funeral hall
and drapes are closed to separate the hall from funeral guests,
assembled in two long tents facing the hall, while the coffin is
placed in the hall.
   _10:53 a.m. (8:53 p.m. EST) _ Forty-seven minute imperial
ceremony begins in which offerings of food and silk cloth are made
to the late emperor. His son and successor, Emperor Akihito, reads a
eulogy.
   _11:40 a.m. (9:40 p.m. EST) _ Offerings are removed and ceremony
ends; drapes are closed and religious decorations removed.
   _11:58 a.m. (9:58 p.m. EST) _ Drapes open and Chief Cabinet
Secretary Keizo Obuchi announces start of 67-minute state funeral
and observance of silence for one minute; Prime Minister Noboru
Takeshita and others to read eulogies; foreign dignitaries walk up
individually to pay last respects.
   _1:31 p.m. (11:31 p.m. EST) _ Coffin is moved to hearse.
   _1:40 p.m. (11:40 p.m. EST) _ Motorcade leaves funeral site for
imperial mauseleum in Hachioji, a western suburb of Tokyo.
   _3:35 p.m. (1:35 a.m. Friday EST) _ Procession arrives at
mausoleum, and after a ceremony the coffin is placed in the tomb.
The ceremony adjourns for three hours while the grave is closed.
   _7:20 p.m. (5:20 a.m. EST) _ Final ceremony is held with
offerings of food; ends at 8:50 p.m. (6:50 a.m. EST).
   Foreign dignitaries participate only in the ceremonies at
Shinjuku Imperial Gardens, which last from 10:15 a.m. to 1:40 p.m.
(8:15 p.m. to 11:30 p.m. EST Thursday).
</TEXT>
