<HEAD>Pair of Legs Found in Garbage Container</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SALT LAKE CITY (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A pair of legs, severed cleanly at the
thigh and wearing different socks, was found in the garbage behind a
grocery store, police said.
   Detectives said they were not certain if they were dealing with a
murder.
   ``We have no idea what we have here,'' said Sheriff's Capt.
Robert Jack. ``It may be something from the university labs.''
   The University of Utah's hospital morgue and anatomy labs found
no indication of missing body parts, said the university's Health
Sciences Center spokeswoman, Anne Brillinger.
   The university has not taken in a fresh cadaver in two weeks, she
said.
   The limbs, discovered Wednesday by a man rummaging for boxes, are
possibly those of a middle-aged man and may have been severed
earlier in the day, Jack said.
</TEXT>
