<NOTE>Following item for release at 6 p.m. EST</NOTE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Actor Gene Hackman says he blocked out most of
his past, including his anger at the father who abandoned him when
he was 13, until his 1970 role in ``I Never Sang For My Father.''
   The role of the estranged son opposite actor Melvyn Douglas
prompted a reconciliation with the father who walked out on Hackman,
his mother and his younger brother.
   Hackman said the resentment may have added to his macho image.
   ``Coming to terms with my father's weakness made me understand
that being strong means being honest,'' Hackman said in the upcoming
issue of Parade magazine.
   Hackman said that for a long time ``I did what a lot of
successful people do, which is to take credit for inventing oneself,
as if the past had nothing to do with it.''
   ``But then I saw myself becoming a Frankenstein monster, mouthing
all the cliches of the so-called, self-made man like _ `I pulled
myself up by my bootstraps' and `I've paid my dues,''' he said.
   Now, Hackman said, ``I realize that it's all part of who I am and
that only by accepting everything I have experienced can I remain
open to change.''
</TEXT>
<DATELINE>ROME (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A tax court Thursday acquitted director Franco
Zeffirelli of tax evasion.
   Zeffirelli was accused of failing to report in 1982 and 1983
nearly 1 billion lire, now worth about $740,000. The director
claimed he was a resident of Tunisia during that period and not
subject to Italian income tax.
   The court upheld Zeffirelli's argument.
   Zeffirelli's films include ``Romeo and Juliet.''
 
</TEXT>
<DATELINE>ST. LOUIS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Composer Marvin Hamlisch plans to marry
independent TV producer Terre Blair on May 29, a spokesman announced
Thursday.
   Hamlisch, 44, is in St. Louis to perform with the St. Louis
Symphony on Friday and Sunday. He was accompanied by Blair, 33, who
has been a sports broadcaster on radio and network TV, spokesman Lee
Solters said.
   Solters said the couple had not decided on a wedding site.
