<HEAD>50 Drown When Bus Plunges into Yangtze</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEIJING (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A bus with faulty brakes careened off a ferry into
the Yangtze River, killing about 50 people, a newspaper said
Thursday.
   The People's Daily said 13 people survived the accident, which
occurred Wednesday on the south bank of China's longest river in
Shashi, Hubei province. More than 60 people were on the bus, it said.
   The daily said the driver of the bus had tried to fix the brakes
while waiting to drive the vehicle aboard the river ferry. But the
brakes gave way and the driver lost control, plunging the bus into
26 feet of water.
