<FIRST>r i AM-Italy-Drugs     02-23 0103</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Italy-Drugs,0105</SECOND>
<HEAD>Fourteen Arrested In International Drug Ring</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ROME (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Police said Thursday they arrested 14 people and
seized 92{ pounds of cocaine to cap investigations of two
international drug rings.
   Investigators believe the suspects seized in the Rome area on
Wednesday and on Feb. 1 were involved in two separate South
America-Italy drug trafficking operations totaling more than $7.4
million, said police spokesman Col. Gennaro Nellio.
   The investigations lasted six months and traced one ring to
Argentina and the other to Colombia, Nellio said. He said both rings
operated about two years and regularly channeled drugs to Italy
through Spain.
</TEXT>
