<FIRST>r i AM-Obit-Jacno     02-23 0134</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Obit-Jacno,0136</SECOND>
<HEAD>Designer of Gauloise Package Dies</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PARIS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Graphic artist Marcel Jacno, who designed the
Gauloises Bleues cigarette package, is dead at age 84, members of
his family reported Thursday.
   They said he died Wednesday in a Paris hospital of a heart
condition.
   Jacno, born in Paris on Aug. 6, 1904, designed labels, posters
and packages familiar to millions of Frenchmen and exported
worldwide. They included the Courvoisier cognac label, the masthead
of the newspaper France Soir and posters for the Comedie Francaise,
Paris Opera and other leading theaters.
   The square, squat Gauloises package, decorated with a winged
helmet and his signature in tiny print in the bottom right corner,
became the most familiar. More than 2 billion packages have been
produced every year since the brand was introduced in 1946.
</TEXT>
