<FIRST>r f PM-NatWestExpansion     02-23 0148</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-NatWest Expansion,0154</SECOND>
<HEAD>National Westminster Buys New Jersey Bank</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   National Westminster Bancorp Inc., a subsidiary
of a British banking concern, has agreed to acquire the First
National Bank of Central Jersey in a cash deal valued at around $282
million.
   The $50-a-share bid disclosed Wednesday is subject to approval
from regulators, including the Federal Reserve Board, and the
shareholders of Ultra Bancorporation, First National's parent
company.
   Ultra Bancorporation, based in Bridgewater, N.J., operates 35
branches and had assets of $1.25 billion at the end of 1988.
   Under the agreement, First National will operate as a subsidiary
of National Westminster and become the second New Jersey bank to
merge with the company in the past year. In February 1988, National
Westminster bought First Jersey National Corp.
   National Westminster, with assets of around $20 billion, is a
wholly owned subsidiary of London-based National Westminster PLC.
</TEXT>
