<FIRST>r f BC-BearStearns     02-23 0182</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Bear Stearns,0188</SECOND>
<HEAD>Investment Firm Starting International Equity Department</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Bear, Stearns &amp; Co. said Thursday it is entering
the international securities research business through its London
subsidiary and initially will concentrate on Europe.
   The investment firm said it is establishing a research office in
London and an international sales and sales-trading group in New
York and London to market new research.
   The firm will focus on industry and country analysis through its
London subsidiary, Bear Stearns International Ltd., the company said
in a statement. Bear Stearns Chairman Alan C. Greenberg said the
expansion comes at a time when other firms are reducing their
presence in the international securities market.
   ``This is the type of climate that Bear Stearns historically has
used for expansion and we are very excited about the possibilities
for growth in this area,'' he said.
   The international securities business will be managed by Duncan
Soukup, a managing director who joined the Bear Stearns late last
year. The firm said it already has hired a group of analysts to
monitor some European countries and industries.
</TEXT>
