<HEAD>Production Goes Down This Week</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: Only version planned.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Domestic automakers were scheduled to produce
238,331 cars and light trucks this week, down from last week's
252,973, Ward's Automotive Reports said Thursday.
   This week's production is higher than the same week a year ago,
in which 215,604 cars and light trucks were produced, the trade
journal said.
   U.S. automakers were scheduled to make 148,464 cars this week,
compared with 157,768 a week ago and 130,744 in the same week in
1988.
   Light truck production for the week was scheduled at 89,867,
compared with last week's 95,205 and last year's 84,860.
   Canadian automakers were to build 22,231 cars this week, up from
20,454 a week ago and from last year's 19,893.
   Canadian light truck production was scheduled at 21,707, compared
with 22,566 a week ago and 20,045 in the same week last year.
