<HEAD>T. Allan McArtor to Re-Join Federal Express</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MEMPHIS, Tenn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   T. Allan McArtor, former administrator of
the Federal Aviation Administration, will return to Federal Express
Corp. as senior vice president of air operations, company officials
said.
   McArtor will assume his duties March 1. He succeeds James
Riedmeyer, who is retiring, officials said Wednesday.
   In 1987, McArtor left Federal Express to become administrator of
the FAA.
   He joined Memphis-based Federal Express in 1979 as vice-president
of systems operations and has served in other positions, including
senior vice president of telecommunications.
   McArtor is a graduate of the U.S. Air Force Academy and obtained
a master's degree in engineering from Arizona State University.
