<FIRST>r f BC-Earns-ICI     02-23 0208</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Earns-ICI,0217</SECOND>
<HEAD>ICI Reports Record Income For 1988</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WILMINGTON, Del. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Imperial Chemical Industries PLC of
London reported its profit for the fourth quarter of 1988 rose 13
percent, while earnings for all of 1988 increased about 10 percent
to a record level.
   ICI, whose American affiliate, ICI Americas Inc., has its
headquarters here, said it earned $369 million, or $2.16 per
American Depository Receipt, in the fourth quarter, compared with a
profit of $324 million, or $1.92 per ADR, in the fourth quarter of
1987.
   Sales for the quarter totaled $5.39 billion, up about 5.5 percent
from the $5.10 billion reported for the fourth quarter of 1987.
   Earnings for 1988 totaled about $1.5 billion, or $8.87 per ADR,
compared with the $1.37 billion, or $8.18 per ADR, reported in 1987.
   Sales in 1988 rose about 5 percent to $21 billion from 1987's
sales of $20 billion.
   Harry Corless, chairman of ICI Americas Inc., said 1988 ``was
another year of rapid progress, with sales up 21 percent (in the
United States) and trading profits up 37 percent (in the United
States) in local currency against the background of a booming U.S.
economy.''
   ICI is involved in industrial chemicals, agricultural chemicals,
biotechnology, pharmaceuticals and consumer products.
</TEXT>
