<FILEID>AP-NR-02-23-89 0116EST</FILEID>
<FIRST>r f BC-Earns-Litton     02-23 0133</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Earns-Litton,0138</SECOND>
<HEAD>Profit Up 7 Percent In 2nd Quarter</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEVERLY HILLS, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Litton Industries Inc., a maker of
ships, automated factory equipment and electronic gear, said its
profit rose 7 percent in both the three months and the six months
ended Jan 31.
   Litton said Wednesday it earned $43.5 million, or $1.71 a share,
in the quarter, up from $40.7 million, or $1.56 a share, in the
three months ended Jan. 31, 1988. Sales for the most recent quarter
were $1.2 billion, up from $1.16 billion a year earlier.
   In the six months ended Jan. 31, profit was $87 million, or $3.40
a share, up from $81.3 million, or $3.07 a share, in the same period
of last year. Sales were $2.43 billion, up from $2.35 billion a year
earlier.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
